  "text": "this end, we prepared serum-free conditioned medium from breast and pancreatic tumor-cell lines, varying in their growth profiles and genomic abnormalities. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Unfractionated (data not shown) and fractionated (< 1 kDa) tumor conditioned media were tested for their ability to promote EC survival under hypoxia. Interestingly, although some cell lines were capable of inducing a short-term survival response in ECs under hypoxia, no long-term survival was seen (Fig. 4d) . Thus, the survival effect mediated by the < 1 kDa fraction seems to be specific for melanoma cells. Under normoxic conditions, EC survival was observed with all breast and pancreatic tumor CM tested (Fig. S3b) .",
